ZH: 车速太快会影响驾驶安全。
EN: Driving at high speeds will affect safety.

ZH: 请务必保持适当的车速。
EN: Please make sure to maintain an appropriate speed.

ZH: 警察在高速公路上监测车速。
EN: Police officers monitor speeds on the highway.

ZH: 如果你违规超速，会被罚款。
EN: You will be fined for speeding.

ZH: 高速公路上的车速限制是多少？
EN: What is the speed limit on the highway?

ZH: 警察在校车前放慢车速。
EN: Police officers slow down speeds in front of school buses.

ZH: 在雨天要降低你的车速。
EN: Reduce your speed in rainy days.

ZH: 刹车时要控制好车速。
EN: Control your speed when braking.

ZH: 路上的车速很慢，造成了交通拥堵。
EN: The slow speeds on the road cause traffic jams.

ZH: 司机可以根据路况适当调整车速。
EN: Drivers can adjust their speeds according to road conditions.

ZH: 别人的车速不是你的标准。
EN: Other people's speeds are not your standard.

ZH: 倒车时要控制好车速。
EN: Control your speed when reversing.

ZH: 在高山区域，要降低车速。
EN: Reduce your speed in mountainous areas.

ZH: 车速过慢可能影响周围车辆。
EN: Driving too slowly may affect surrounding vehicles.

ZH: 提高车速以赶上前面的车辆。
EN: Increase speed to catch up with the vehicle ahead.

ZH: 别被车速快的人影响你的判断。
EN: Don't let fast drivers influence your judgment.

ZH: 驾驶员必须时刻注意车速。
EN: Drivers must pay attention to their speed at all times.

ZH: 请控制好车速以避免事故发生。
EN: Please control your speed to avoid accidents.

ZH: 车速超过限制会受到处罚。
EN: Exceeding speed limits will result in penalties.

ZH: 注意保持合适的车速以确保行车安全。
EN: Be sure to maintain a proper speed to ensure road safety.
